U.K. Stocks Decline; Admiral, Amec, Marks & Spencer Lead FTSE 100 Lower

-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 
2011-08-25T13:51:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/u-k-stocks-decline-admiral-amec-marks-spencer-lead-ftse-100-lower.html
U.K. stocks fell, led by Admiral
Group Plc, AMEC Plc and Marks & Spencer Group Plc.  The benchmark FTSE 100 Index lost 24.15, or 0.5 percent, to
5,181.70 as of 2:51 p.m. in  London . The measure of British
shares has fallen as much as 0.6 percent today and has climbed
as much as 0.9 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
